16/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The Netherlands, current holder of the rotating EU presidency, issued a statement on behalf of the Union criticising the reform process in Albania, local media reported Wednesday (15 September). The statement cited the country's problems in dealing with widespread corruption and organised crime. It also criticised delays in electoral reform. The OSCE Presence in Albania said it fully supports the EU statement, and urged the country's political parties to join forces and reach lasting solutions to political issues. 
In other news, the OSCE Presence and Albania's Labour and Social Affairs Ministry will hold a donor conference Thursday on the problems faced by disabled people. Tirana recently prepared a national strategy for assisting people with disabilities, addressing employment, accessibility, education and services. (OSCE press release, Albanian Daily News, ATA - 16/09/04; ATA - 15/09/04) 
